The paper focuses on the problem of visual speech recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The dataset is large-scale and involves a variety of imaging conditions, which suggests that it may be relevant to computer graphics (cs.SD) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper evaluates several popular lipreading methods, which suggests that it may be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
